The paper proposes a novel mechanism for preserving differential privacy in deep neural networks, with a focus on improving robustness against adversarial attacks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as privacy and security are key concerns. The paper also involves techniques related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and social and information networks (cs.SI), which are also possible sub-categories.
